  <Name>k__BackingField: Proverbs
  fancyName: 
  nickname: pro
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Usefulness of Proverbs'
      title: The Usefulness of Proverbs
      number: 1
      content: '  The proverbs (truths obscurely expressed, maxims) of Solomon son
        of David, king of Israel:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'To know [skillful and godly] wisdom and instruction;To discern and
        comprehend the words of understanding and insight,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'To receive instruction in wise behavior and the discipline of wise
        thoughtfulness,Righteousness, justice, and integrity;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'That prudence (good judgment, astute common sense) may be given to
        the naive or inexperienced [who are easily misled],And knowledge and discretion
        (intelligent discernment) to the youth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The wise will hear and increase their learning,And the person of
        understanding will acquire wise counsel and the skill [to steer his course
        wisely and lead others to the truth],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'To understand a proverb and a figure [of speech] or an enigma with
        its interpretation,And the words of the wise and their riddles [that require
        reflection].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Enticement of Sinners'
      title: The Enticement of Sinners
      number: 7
      content: 'The [reverent] fear of the Lord [that is, worshiping Him and regarding
        Him as truly awesome] is the beginning and the preeminent part of knowledge
        [its starting point and its essence];  But arrogant  fools despise [skillful
        and godly] wisdom and instruction and self-discipline.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'My son, hear the instruction of your father,And do not reject the
        teaching of your mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For they are a garland of grace on your head,And chains and ornaments
        [of gold] around your neck.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'My son, if sinners entice you,Do not consent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "If they say, \u201CCome with us;Let us lie in wait to shed blood,Let
        us ambush the innocent without cause;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let us swallow them alive like Sheol (the place of the dead),Even
        whole, as those who go down to the pit [of death];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'We will find and take all kinds of precious possessions,We will fill
        our houses with spoil;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Throw in your lot with us [they insist];We will all have one money
        bag [in common],\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My son, do not walk on the road with them;Keep your foot [far] away
        from their path,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For their feet run to evil,And they hurry to shed blood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Indeed, it is useless to spread the baited netIn the sight of any
        bird;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But [when these people set a trap for others] they lie in wait for
        their own blood;They set an ambush for their own lives [and rush to their
        destruction].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Wisdom Warns'
      title: Wisdom Warns
      number: 19
      content: 'So are the ways of everyone who is greedy for gain;Greed takes away
        the lives of its possessors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Wisdom shouts in the street,She raises her voice in the markets;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'She calls out at the head of the noisy streets [where large crowds
        gather];At the entrance of the city gates she speaks her words:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CHow long, O naive ones [you who are easily misled], will you
        love being simple-minded and undiscerning?  How long will scoffers [who ridicule
        and deride] delight in scoffing,  How long will fools [who obstinately mock
        truth] hate knowledge?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If you will turn and pay attention to my rebuke,Behold, I [Wisdom]
        will pour out my spirit on you;I will make my words known to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Because I called and you refused [to answer],I stretched out my hand
        and no one has paid attention [to my offer];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And you treated all my counsel as nothingAnd would not accept my
        reprimand,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I also will laugh at your disaster;I will mock when your dread and
        panic come,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When your dread and panic come like a storm,And your disaster comes
        like a whirlwind,When anxiety and distress come upon you [as retribution].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Then they will call upon me (Wisdom), but I will not answer;They
        will seek me eagerly but they will not find me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Because they hated knowledgeAnd did not choose the fear of the Lord
        [that is, obeying Him with reverence and awe-filled respect],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'They would not accept my counsel,And they spurned all my rebuke.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Therefore they shall eat of the fruit of their own [wicked] wayAnd
        be satiated with [the penalty of] their own devices.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For the turning away of the naive will kill them,And the careless
        ease of [self-righteous] fools will destroy them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "But whoever listens to me (Wisdom) will live securely and in confident
        trustAnd will be at ease, without fear or dread of evil.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Pursuit of Wisdom Brings Security'
      title: The Pursuit of Wisdom Brings Security
      number: 1
      content: '  My son, if you will receive my wordsAnd treasure my commandments
        within you,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So that your ear is attentive to [skillful and godly] wisdom,And
        apply your heart to understanding [seeking it conscientiously and striving
        for it eagerly];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Yes, if you cry out for insight,And lift up your voice for understanding;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'If you seek skillful and godly wisdom as you would silverAnd search
        for her as you would hidden treasures;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then you will understand the [reverent] fear of the Lord [that is,
        worshiping Him and regarding Him as truly awesome]And discover the knowledge
        of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the Lord gives [skillful and godly] wisdom;From His mouth come
        knowledge and understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He stores away sound wisdom for the righteous [those who are in right
        standing with Him];  He is a shield to those who walk in integrity [those
        of honorable character and moral courage],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He guards the paths of justice;And He preserves the way of His saints
        (believers).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then you will understand righteousness and justice [in every circumstance]And
        integrity and every good path.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For [skillful and godly] wisdom will enter your heartAnd knowledge
        will be pleasant to your soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Discretion will watch over you,Understanding and discernment will
        guard you,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'To keep you from the way of evil and the evil man,From the man who
        speaks perverse things;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'From those who leave the paths of uprightnessTo walk in the ways
        of darkness;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who find joy in doing evilAnd delight in the perversity of evil,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Whose paths are crooked,And who are devious in their ways;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'To keep you from the immoral woman;From the seductress with her flattering
        words,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Who leaves the companion (husband) of her youth,And forgets the covenant
        of her God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For her house leads down to deathAnd her paths lead to the dead;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "None who go to her return again,Nor do they regain the paths of life\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So you will walk in the way of good men [that is, those of personal
        integrity, moral courage and honorable character],And keep to the paths of
        the righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For the upright [those who are in right standing with God] will live
        in the landAnd those [of integrity] who are blameless [in God\u2019s sight]
        will remain in it;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: But the wicked will be cut off from the landAnd the treacherous shall
        be [forcibly] uprooted and removed from it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Rewards of Wisdom'
      title: The Rewards of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: '  My son, do not forget my teaching,But let your heart keep my commandments;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For length of days and years of life [worth living]And tranquility
        and prosperity [the wholeness of life\u2019s blessings] they will add to
        you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do not let mercy and kindness and truth leave you [instead let these
        qualities define you];Bind them [securely] around your neck,Write them on
        the tablet of your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So find favor and high esteemIn the sight of God and man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Trust in and rely confidently on the Lord with all your heartAnd
        do not rely on your own insight or understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  In all your ways know and acknowledge and recognize Him,And He
        will make your paths straight and smooth [removing obstacles that block your
        way].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Do not be wise in your own eyes;Fear the Lord [with reverent awe
        and obedience] and turn [entirely] away from evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "It will be health to your body [your marrow, your nerves, your sinews,
        your muscles\u2014all your inner parts]And refreshment (physical well-being)
        to your bones.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Honor the Lord with your wealthAnd with the first fruits of all your
        crops (income);  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then your barns will be abundantly filledAnd your vats will overflow
        with new wine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My son, do not reject or take lightly the discipline of the Lord
        [learn from your mistakes and the testing that comes from His correction
        through discipline];Nor despise His rebuke,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For those whom the Lord loves He corrects,Even as a father corrects
        the son in whom he delights.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Happy [blessed, considered fortunate, to be admired] is the man who
        finds [skillful and godly] wisdom,And the man who gains understanding and
        insight [learning from God\u2019s word and life\u2019s experiences],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For wisdom\u2019s profit is better than the profit of silver,And
        her gain is better than fine gold.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'She is more precious than rubies;And nothing you can wish for compares
        with her [in value].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Long life is in her right hand;In her left hand are riches and honor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Her ways are highways of pleasantness and favor,And all her paths
        are peace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'She is a tree of life to those who take hold of her,And happy [blessed,
        considered fortunate, to be admired] is everyone who holds her tightly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The Lord by His wisdom has founded the earth;By His understanding
        He has established the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'By His knowledge the deeps were broken upAnd the clouds drip with
        dew.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'My son, let them not escape from your sight,But keep sound wisdom
        and discretion,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And they will be life to your soul (your inner self)And a gracious
        adornment to your neck (your outer self).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then you will walk on your way [of life] securelyAnd your foot will
        not stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When you lie down, you will not be afraid;When you lie down, your
        sleep will be sweet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Do not be afraid of sudden fearNor of the storm of the wicked when
        it comes [since you will be blameless];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For the Lord will be your confidence, firm and strong,And will keep
        your foot from being caught [in a trap].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  Do not withhold good from those to whom it is due [its rightful
        recipients],When it is in your power to do it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Do not say to your neighbor, \u201CGo, and come back,And tomorrow
        I will give it,\u201DWhen you have it with you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Do not devise evil against your neighbor,Who lives securely beside
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Do not quarrel with a man without cause,If he has done you no harm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Do not envy a man of violenceAnd do not choose any of his ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For the devious are repulsive to the Lord;But His private counsel
        is with the upright [those with spiritual integrity and moral courage].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The curse of the Lord is on the house of the wicked,But He blesses
        the home of the just and righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Though He scoffs at the scoffers and scorns the scorners,Yet He gives
        His grace [His undeserved favor] to the humble [those who give up self-importance].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: The wise will inherit honor and glory,But dishonor and shame is conferred
        on fools.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: A Father\u2019s Instruction"
      title: "A Father\u2019s Instruction"
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear, O children, the instruction of a father,And pay attention
        [and be willing to learn] so that you may gain understanding and intelligent
        discernment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For I give you good doctrine;Do not turn away from my instruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When I was a son with my father (David),Tender and the only son in
        the sight of my mother (Bathsheba),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He taught me and said to me,\u201CLet your heart hold fast my words;Keep
        my commandments and live.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Get [skillful and godly] wisdom! Acquire understanding [actively
        seek spiritual discernment, mature comprehension, and logical interpretation]!Do
        not forget nor turn away from the words of my mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do not turn away from her (Wisdom) and she will guard and protect
        you;Love her, and she will watch over you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The beginning of wisdom is: Get [skillful and godly] wisdom [it is
        preeminent]!And with all your acquiring, get understanding [actively seek
        spiritual discernment, mature comprehension, and logical interpretation].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Prize wisdom [and exalt her], and she will exalt you;She will honor
        you if you embrace her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "She will place on your head a garland of grace;She will present you
        with a crown of beauty and glory.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Hear, my son, and accept my sayings,And the years of your life will
        be many.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I have instructed you in the way of [skillful and godly] wisdom;I
        have led you in upright paths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When you walk, your steps will not be impeded [for your path will
        be clear and open];And when you run, you will not stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Take hold of instruction; [actively seek it, grip it firmly and]
        do not let go.Guard her, for she is your life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Do not enter the path of the wicked,And do not go the way of evil
        men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Avoid it, do not travel on it;Turn away from it and pass on.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For the wicked cannot sleep unless they do evil;And they are deprived
        of sleep unless they make someone stumble and fall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For they eat the bread of wickednessAnd drink the wine of violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But the path of the just (righteous) is like the light of dawn,That
        shines brighter and brighter until [it reaches its full strength and glory
        in] the perfect day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The way of the wicked is like [deep] darkness;They do not know over
        what they stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My son, pay attention to my words and be willing to learn;Open your
        ears to my sayings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Do not let them escape from your sight;Keep them in the center of
        your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For they are life to those who find them,And healing and health to
        all their flesh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Watch over your heart with all diligence,For from it flow the springs
        of life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Put away from you a deceitful (lying, misleading) mouth,And put devious
        lips far from you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Let your eyes look directly ahead [toward the path of moral courage]And
        let your gaze be fixed straight in front of you [toward the path of integrity].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Consider well and watch carefully the path of your feet,And all your
        ways will be steadfast and sure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Do not turn away to the right nor to the left [where evil may lurk];Turn
        your foot from [the path of] evil.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Pitfalls of Immorality'
      title: Pitfalls of Immorality
      number: 1
      content: '  My son, be attentive to my wisdom [godly wisdom learned by costly
        experience],Incline your ear to my understanding;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'That you may exercise discrimination and discretion (good judgment),And
        your lips may reserve knowledge and answer wisely [to temptation].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the lips of an immoral woman drip honey [like a honeycomb]And
        her speech is smoother than oil;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But in the end she is bitter like [the extract of] wormwood,Sharp
        as a two-edged sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Her feet go down to death;Her steps take hold of Sheol (the nether
        world, the place of the dead),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So that she does not think [seriously] about the path of life;Her
        ways are aimless and unstable; you cannot know where her path leads.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now then, my sons, listen to meAnd do not depart from (forget) the
        words of my mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Let your way [in life] be far from her,And do not go near the door
        of her house [avoid even being near the places of temptation],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Or you will give your honor to others,And your years to the cruel
        one,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And strangers will be filled with your strengthAnd your hard-earned
        wealth will go to the house of a foreigner [who does not know God];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you will groan when your life is ending,When your flesh and your
        body are consumed;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And you say, \u201CHow I hated instruction and discipline,And my
        heart despised correction and reproof!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I have not listened to the voice of my teachers,Nor have I inclined
        my ear to those who instructed me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I was almost in total ruinIn the midst of the assembly and congregation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Drink water from your own cistern [of a pure marriage relationship]And
        fresh running water from your own well.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Should your springs (children) be dispersed,As streams of water in
        the streets?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '[Confine yourself to your own wife.] Let your children be yours alone,And
        not the children of strangers with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Let your fountain (wife) be blessed [with the rewards of fidelity],And
        rejoice in the wife of your youth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Let her be as a loving hind and graceful doe,Let her breasts refresh
        and satisfy you at all times;Always be exhilarated and delight in her love.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Why should you, my son, be exhilarated with an immoral womanAnd embrace
        the bosom of an outsider (pagan)?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the ways of man are directly before the eyes of the Lord,And
        He carefully watches all of his paths [all of his comings and goings].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The iniquities done by a wicked man will trap him,And he will be
        held with the cords of his sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: He will die for lack of instruction (discipline),And in the greatness
        of his foolishness he will go astray and be lost.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Parental Counsel'
      title: Parental Counsel
      number: 1
      content: '  My son, if you have become surety (guaranteed a debt or obligation)
        for your neighbor,If you have given your pledge for [the debt of] a stranger
        or another [outside your family],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'If you have been snared with the words of your lips,If you have been
        trapped by the speech of your mouth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do this now, my son, and release yourself [from the obligation]; 
        Since you have come into the hand of your neighbor,Go humble yourself, and
        plead with your neighbor [to pay his debt and release you].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Give no [unnecessary] sleep to your eyes,Nor slumber to your eyelids;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Tear yourself away like a gazelle from the hand of the hunterAnd
        like a bird from the hand of the fowler.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Go to the ant, O lazy one;Observe her ways and be wise,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Which, having no chief,Overseer or ruler,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'She prepares her food in the summerAnd brings in her provisions [of
        food for the winter] in the harvest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'How long will you lie down, O lazy one?When will you arise from your
        sleep [and learn self-discipline]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYet a little sleep, a little slumber,A little folding of the
        hands to lie down and rest\u201D\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So your poverty will come like an approaching prowler who walks [slowly,
        but surely]And your need [will come] like an armed man [making you helpless].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A worthless person, a wicked man,Is one who walks with a perverse
        (corrupt, vulgar) mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who winks with his eyes [in mockery], who shuffles his feet [to signal],Who
        points with his fingers [to give subversive instruction];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who perversely in his heart plots trouble and evil continually;Who
        spreads discord and strife.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore [the crushing weight of] his disaster will come suddenly
        upon him;Instantly he will be broken, and there will be no healing or remedy
        [because he has no heart for God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These six things the Lord hates;Indeed, seven are repulsive to Him:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'A proud look [the attitude that makes one overestimate oneself and
        discount others], a lying tongue,And hands that shed innocent blood,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'A heart that creates wicked plans,Feet that run swiftly to evil,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'A false witness who breathes out lies [even half-truths],And one
        who spreads discord (rumors) among brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "My son, be guided by your father\u2019s [God-given] commandment (instruction)And
        do not reject the teaching of your mother;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Bind them continually upon your heart (in your thoughts),And tie
        them around your neck.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'When you walk about, they (the godly teachings of your parents) will
        guide you;When you sleep, they will keep watch over you;And when you awake,
        they will talk to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the commandment is a lamp, and the teaching [of the law] is light,And
        reproofs (rebukes) for discipline are the way of life,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'To keep you from the evil woman,From [the flattery of] the smooth
        tongue of an immoral woman.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Do not desire (lust after) her beauty in your heart,Nor let her capture
        you with her eyelashes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For on account of a prostitute one is reduced to a piece of bread
        [to be eaten up],And the immoral woman hunts [with a hook] the precious life
        [of a man].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Can a man take fire to his chestAnd his clothes not be burned?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Or can a man walk on hot coalsAnd his feet not be scorched?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So is the one who goes in to his neighbor\u2019s wife;Whoever touches
        her will not be found innocent or go unpunished.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'People do not despise a thief if he stealsTo satisfy himself when
        he is hungry;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'But when he is found, he must repay seven times [what he stole];He
        must give all the property of his house [if necessary to meet his fine].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'But whoever commits adultery with a woman lacks common sense and
        sound judgment and an understanding [of moral principles];He who would destroy
        his soul does it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Wounds and disgrace he will find,And his reproach (blame) will not
        be blotted out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'For jealousy enrages the [wronged] husband;He will not spare [the
        guilty one] on the day of vengeance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: He will not accept any ransom [offered to buy him off from demanding
        full punishment];Nor will he be satisfied though you offer him many gifts
        (bribes).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wiles of the Prostitute'
      title: The Wiles of the Prostitute
      number: 1
      content: '  My son, keep my wordsAnd treasure my commandments within you [so
        they are readily available to guide you].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Keep my commandments and live,And keep my teaching and law as the
        apple of your eye.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Bind them [securely] on your fingers;Write them on the tablet of
        your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Say to [skillful and godly] wisdom, \u201CYou are my sister,\u201DAnd
        regard understanding and intelligent insight as your intimate friends;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "That they may keep you from the immoral woman,From the foreigner
        [who does not observe God\u2019s laws and] who flatters with her [smooth]
        words.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For at the window of my houseI looked out through my lattice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And among the naive [the inexperienced and gullible],I saw among
        the youthsA young man lacking [good] sense,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Passing through the street near her corner;And he took the path to
        her house  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In the twilight, in the evening;In the black and dark night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And there a woman met him,Dressed as a prostitute and sly and cunning
        of heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'She was boisterous and rebellious;  She would not stay at home.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'At times she was in the streets, at times in the market places,Lurking
        and setting her ambush at every corner.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So she caught him and kissed himAnd with a brazen and impudent face
        she said to him:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CI have peace offerings with me;Today I have paid my vows.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So I came out to meet you [that you might share with me the feast
        of my offering],Diligently I sought your face and I have found you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I have spread my couch with coverings and cushions of tapestry,With
        colored fine linen of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I have perfumed my bedWith myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Come, let us drink our fill of love until morning;Let us console
        and delight ourselves with love.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For my husband is not at home.He has gone on a long journey;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He has taken a bag of money with him,And he will come home on the
        appointed day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'With her many persuasions she caused him to yield;With her flattering
        lips she seduced him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Suddenly he went after her, as an ox goes to the slaughter [not knowing
        the outcome],Or as one in stocks going to the correction [to be given] to
        a fool,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Until an arrow pierced his liver [with a mortal wound];Like a bird
        fluttering straight into the net,He did not know that it would cost him his
        life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now therefore, my sons, listen to me,And pay attention to the words
        of my mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Do not let your heart turn aside to her ways,Do not stray into her
        [evil, immoral] paths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For she has cast down many [mortally] wounded;Indeed, all who were
        killed by her were strong.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Her house is the way to Sheol,Descending to the chambers of death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Commendation of Wisdom'
      title: The Commendation of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: '  Does not wisdom call,And understanding lift up her voice?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'On the top of the heights beside the way,Where the paths meet, wisdom
        takes her stand;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Beside the gates, at the entrance to the city,At the entrance of
        the doors, she cries out:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTo you, O men, I call,And my voice is directed to the sons
        of men.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'O you naive or inexperienced [who are easily misled], understand
        prudence and seek astute common sense;And, O you [closed-minded, self-confident]
        fools, understand wisdom [seek the insight and self-discipline that leads
        to godly living].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Listen, for I will speak excellent and noble things;And the opening
        of my lips will reveal right things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For my mouth will utter truth,And wickedness is repulsive and loathsome
        to my lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All the words of my mouth are in righteousness (upright, in right
        standing with God);There is nothing contrary to truth or perverted (crooked)
        in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They are all straightforward to him who understands [with an open
        and willing mind],And right to those who find knowledge and live by it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Take my instruction rather than [seeking] silver,And take knowledge
        rather than choicest gold,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For wisdom is better than rubies;And all desirable things cannot
        compare with her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI, [godly] wisdom, reside with prudence [good judgment, moral
        courage and astute common sense],And I find knowledge and discretion.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The [reverent] fear and worshipful awe of the Lord  includes the
        hatred of evil;Pride and arrogance and the evil way,And the perverted mouth,
        I hate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Counsel is mine and sound wisdom;I am understanding, power and strength
        are mine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'By me kings reignAnd rulers decide and decree justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'By me princes rule, and nobles,All who judge and govern rightly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I love those who love me;And those who seek me early and diligently
        will find me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Riches and honor are with me,Enduring wealth and righteousness (right
        standing with God).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'My fruit is better than gold, even pure gold,And my yield is better
        than choicest silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I, [Wisdom, continuously] walk in the way of righteousness,In the
        midst of the paths of justice,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'That I may cause those who love me to inherit wealth and true riches,And
        that I may fill their treasuries.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThe Lord created and possessed me at the beginning of His way,Before
        His works of old [were accomplished].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'From everlasting I was established and ordained,From the beginning,
        before the earth existed, [I, godly wisdom, existed].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When there were no ocean depths I was born,When there were no fountains
        and springs overflowing with water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Before the mountains were settled,Before the hills, I was born;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'While He had not yet made the earth and the fields,Or the first of
        the dust of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When He established the heavens, I [Wisdom] was there;When He drew
        a circle upon the face of the deep,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When He made firm the skies above,When the fountains and springs
        of the deep became fixed and strong,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "When He set for the sea its boundarySo that the waters would not
        transgress [the boundaries set by] His command,When He marked out the foundations
        of the earth\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then I was beside Him, as a master craftsman;And I was daily His
        delight;Rejoicing before Him always,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Rejoicing in the world, His inhabited earth,And having my delight
        in the sons of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CNow therefore, O sons, listen to me,For blessed [happy, prosperous,
        to be admired] are they who keep my ways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Heed (pay attention to) instruction and be wise,And do not ignore
        or neglect it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Blessed [happy, prosperous, to be admired] is the man who listens
        to me,Watching daily at my gates,Waiting at my doorposts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'For whoever finds me (Wisdom) finds lifeAnd obtains favor and grace
        from the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "But he who fails to find me or sins against me injures himself;All
        those who hate me love and court death.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Wisdom\u2019s Invitation"
      title: "Wisdom\u2019s Invitation"
      number: 1
      content: '  Wisdom has built her [spacious and sufficient] house;She has hewn
        out and set up her seven pillars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'She has prepared her food, she has mixed her wine;She has also set
        her table.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'She has sent out her maidens, she callsFrom the highest places of
        the city:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CWhoever is naive or inexperienced, let him turn in here!\u201DAs
        for him who lacks understanding, she says,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CCome, eat my foodAnd drink the wine I have mixed [and accept
        my gifts].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Leave [behind] your foolishness [and the foolish] and live,And walk
        in the way of insight and understanding.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He who corrects and instructs a scoffer gets dishonor for himself,And
        he who rebukes a wicked man gets insults for himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Do not correct a scoffer [who foolishly ridicules and takes no
        responsibility for his error] or he will hate you;Correct a wise man [who
        learns from his error], and he will love you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Give instruction to a wise man and he will become even wiser;Teach
        a righteous man and he will increase his learning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The [reverent] fear of the Lord [that is, worshiping Him and regarding
        Him as truly awesome] is the beginning and the preeminent part of wisdom
        [its starting point and its essence],And the knowledge of the Holy One is
        understanding and spiritual insight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For by me (wisdom from God) your days will be multiplied,And years
        of life shall be increased.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'If you are wise, you are wise for yourself [for your own benefit];If
        you scoff [thoughtlessly ridicule and disdain], you alone will pay the penalty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The foolish woman is restless and noisy;She is naive and easily misled
        and thoughtless, and knows nothing at all [of eternal value].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'She sits at the doorway of her house,On a seat by the high and conspicuous
        places of the city,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Calling to those who pass by,Who are making their paths straight:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CWhoever is naive or inexperienced, let him turn in here!\u201DAnd
        to him who lacks understanding (common sense), she says,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CStolen waters (pleasures) are sweet [because they are forbidden];And
        bread eaten in secret is pleasant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: But he does not know that the spirits of the dead are there,And that
        her guests are [already] in the depths of Sheol (the nether world, the place
        of the dead).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Contrast of the Righteous and the Wicked'
      title: Contrast of the Righteous and the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: '  The proverbs of Solomon:A wise son makes a father glad,But a foolish
        [stubborn] son [who refuses to learn] is a grief to his mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Treasures of wickedness and ill-gotten gains do not profit,But righteousness
        and moral integrity in daily life rescues from death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The Lord will not allow the righteous to hunger [God will meet all
        his needs],But He will reject and cast away the craving of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Poor is he who works with a negligent and idle hand,But the hand
        of the diligent makes him rich.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He who gathers during summer and takes advantage of his opportunities
        is a son who acts wisely,  But he who sleeps during harvest and ignores the
        moment of opportunity is a son who acts shamefully.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Blessings are on the head of the righteous [the upright, those in
        right standing with God],But the mouth of the wicked conceals violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The memory of the righteous [person] is a [source of] blessing,But
        the name of the wicked will [be forgotten and] rot [like a corpse].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The wise in heart [are willing to learn so they] will accept and
        obey commands (instruction),But the babbling fool [who is arrogant and thinks
        himself wise] will come to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He who walks in integrity and with moral character walks securely,But
        he who takes a crooked way will be discovered and punished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He who [maliciously] winks the eye [of evil intent] causes trouble;And
        the babbling fool [who is arrogant and thinks himself wise] will come to
        ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The mouth of the righteous is a fountain of life and his words of
        wisdom are a source of blessing,But the mouth of the wicked conceals violence
        and evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Hatred stirs up strife,But love covers and overwhelms all transgressions
        [forgiving and overlooking another\u2019s faults].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'On the lips of the discerning, [skillful and godly] wisdom is found,But
        discipline and the rod are for the back of the one who is without common
        sense and understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Wise men store up and treasure knowledge [in mind and heart],But
        with the mouth of the foolish, ruin is at hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The rich man\u2019s wealth is his fortress;The ruin of the poor is
        their poverty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The wages of the righteous [the upright, those in right standing
        with God] is [a worthwhile, meaningful] life,The income of the wicked, punishment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He who learns from instruction and correction is on the [right] path
        of life [and for others his example is a path toward wisdom and blessing],But
        he who ignores and refuses correction goes off course [and for others his
        example is a path toward sin and ruin].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He who hides hatred has lying lips,And he who spreads slander is
        a fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'When there are many words, transgression and offense are unavoidable,But
        he who controls his lips and keeps thoughtful silence is wise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The tongue of the righteous is like precious silver (greatly valued);The
        heart of the wicked is worth little.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The lips of the righteous feed and guide many,But fools [who reject
        God and His wisdom] die for lack of understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The blessing of the Lord brings [true] riches,And He adds no sorrow
        to it [for it comes as a blessing from God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Engaging in evil is like sport to the fool [who refuses wisdom and
        chases sin],But to a man of understanding [skillful and godly] wisdom brings
        joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'What the wicked fears will come upon him,But the desire of the righteous
        [for the blessings of God] will be granted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When the whirlwind passes, the wicked is no more,But the righteous
        has an everlasting foundation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Like vinegar to the teeth and smoke to the eyes,So is the lazy one
        to those who send him to work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "The [reverent] fear of the Lord [worshiping, obeying, serving, and
        trusting Him with awe-filled respect] prolongs one\u2019s life,But the years
        of the wicked will be shortened.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The hope of the righteous [those of honorable character and integrity]
        is joy,But the expectation of the wicked [those who oppose God and ignore
        His wisdom] comes to nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The way of the Lord is a stronghold to the upright,But it is ruin
        to those who do evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The [consistently] righteous will never be shaken,But the wicked
        will not inhabit the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The mouth of the righteous flows with [skillful and godly] wisdom,But
        the perverted tongue will be cut out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: The lips of the righteous know (speak) what is acceptable,But the
        mouth of the wicked knows (speaks) what is perverted (twisted).
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked'
      title: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: '  A false balance and dishonest business practices are extremely
        offensive to the Lord,But an accurate scale is His delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When pride comes [boiling up with an arrogant attitude of self-importance],
        then come dishonor and shame,But with the humble [the teachable who have
        been chiseled by trial and who have learned to walk humbly with God] there
        is wisdom and soundness of mind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The integrity and moral courage of the upright will guide them,But
        the crookedness of the treacherous will destroy them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Riches will not provide security in the day of wrath and judgment,But
        righteousness rescues from death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The righteousness of the blameless will smooth their way and keep
        it straight,But the wicked will fall by his own wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The righteousness of the upright will rescue them,But the treacherous
        will be caught by their own greed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When the wicked man dies, his expectation will perish;And the hope
        of [godless] strong men perishes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The righteous is rescued from trouble,And the wicked takes his
        place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'With his mouth the godless man destroys his neighbor,But through
        knowledge and discernment the righteous will be rescued.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When it goes well for the righteous, the city rejoices,And when the
        wicked perish, there are shouts of joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'By the blessing [of the influence] of the upright the city is exalted,But
        by the mouth of the wicked it is torn down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He who despises his neighbor lacks sense,But a man of understanding
        keeps silent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He who goes about as a gossip reveals secrets,But he who is trustworthy
        and faithful keeps a matter hidden.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Where there is no [wise, intelligent] guidance, the people fall [and
        go off course like a ship without a helm],But in the abundance of [wise and
        godly] counselors there is victory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He who puts up security and guarantees a debt for an outsider will
        surely suffer [for his foolishness],But he who hates (declines) being a guarantor
        is secure [from its penalties].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'A gracious and good woman attains honor,And ruthless men attain riches
        [but not respect].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The merciful and generous man benefits his soul [for his behavior
        returns to bless him],But the cruel and callous man does himself harm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The wicked man earns deceptive wages,But he who sows righteousness
        and lives his life with integrity will have a true reward [that is both permanent
        and satisfying].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He who is steadfast in righteousness attains life,But he who pursues
        evil attains his own death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The perverse in heart are repulsive and shamefully vile to the Lord,But
        those who are blameless and above reproach in their walk are His delight!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Assuredly, the evil man will not go unpunished,But the descendants
        of the righteous will be freed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "As a ring of gold in a swine\u2019s snout,So is a beautiful woman
        who is without discretion [her lack of character mocks her beauty].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The desire of the righteous brings only good,But the expectation
        of the wicked brings wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'There is the one who [generously] scatters [abroad], and yet increases
        all the more;And there is the one who withholds what is justly due, but it
        results only in want and poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The generous man [is a source of blessing and] shall be prosperous
        and enriched,And he who waters will himself be watered [reaping the generosity
        he has sown].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The people curse him who holds back grain [when the public needs
        it],But a blessing [from God and man] is upon the head of him who sells it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He who diligently seeks good seeks favor and grace,But he who seeks
        evil, evil will come to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "He who leans on and trusts in and is confident in his riches will
        fall,But the righteous [who trust in God\u2019s provision] will flourish
        like a green leaf.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He who troubles (mismanages) his own house will inherit the wind
        (nothing),And the foolish will be a servant to the wise-hearted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The fruit of the [consistently] righteous is a tree of life,And he
        who is wise captures and wins souls [for God\u2014he gathers them for eternity].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: If the righteous will be rewarded on the earth [with godly blessings],How
        much more [will] the wicked and the sinner [be repaid with punishment]!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked'
      title: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: '  Whoever loves instruction and discipline loves knowledge,But he
        who hates reproof and correction is stupid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A good man will obtain favor from the Lord,But He will condemn a
        man who devises evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'A man will not be established by wickedness,But the root of the [consistently]
        righteous will not be moved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'A virtuous and excellent wife [worthy of honor] is the crown of her
        husband,But she who shames him [with her foolishness] is like rottenness
        in his bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The thoughts and purposes of the [consistently] righteous are just
        (honest, reliable),But the counsels and schemes of the wicked are deceitful.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The [malevolent] words of the wicked lie in wait for [innocent] blood
        [to slander],But the mouth of the upright will rescue and protect them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The wicked are overthrown [by their evil] and are no more,But the
        house of the [consistently] righteous will stand [securely].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'A man will be commended according to his insight and sound judgment,But
        the one who is of a perverse mind will be despised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Better is he who is lightly esteemed and has a servant,Than he
        who [boastfully] honors himself [pretending to be what he is not] and lacks
        bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'A righteous man has kind regard for the life of his animal,But even
        the compassion of the wicked is cruel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He who tills his land will have plenty of bread,But he who follows
        worthless things lacks common sense and good judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The wicked desire the plunder of evil men,But the root of the righteous
        yields richer fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'An evil man is [dangerously] ensnared by the transgression of his
        lips,But the righteous will escape from trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "A man will be satisfied with good from the fruit of his words,And
        the deeds of a man\u2019s hands will return to him [as a harvest].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The way of the [arrogant] fool [who rejects God\u2019s wisdom] is
        right in his own eyes,But a wise and prudent man is he who listens to counsel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The [arrogant] fool\u2019s anger is quickly known [because he lacks
        self-control and common sense],But a prudent man ignores an insult.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He who speaks truth [when he testifies] tells what is right,But a
        false witness utters deceit [in court].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There is one who speaks rashly like the thrusts of a sword,But the
        tongue of the wise brings healing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Truthful lips will be established forever,But a lying tongue is [credited]
        only for a moment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Deceit is in the heart of those who devise evil,But counselors of
        peace have joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'No harm befalls the righteous,But the wicked are filled with trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Lying lips are extremely disgusting to the Lord,But those who deal
        faithfully are His delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'A shrewd man is reluctant to display his knowledge [until the proper
        time],But the heart of [over-confident] fools proclaims foolishness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The hand of the diligent will rule,But the negligent and lazy will
        be put to forced labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Anxiety in a man\u2019s heart weighs it down,But a good (encouraging)
        word makes it glad.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The righteous man is a guide to his neighbor,But the way of the wicked
        leads them astray.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The lazy man does not catch and roast his prey,But the precious possession
        of a [wise] man is diligence [because he recognizes opportunities and seizes
        them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "In the way of righteousness is life,And in its pathway there is no
        death [but immortality\u2014eternal life]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked'
      title: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: "  A wise son heeds and accepts [and is the result of] his father\u2019s
        discipline and instruction,But a scoffer does not listen to reprimand and
        does not learn from his errors.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'From the fruit of his mouth a [wise] man enjoys good,But the desire
        of the treacherous is for violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The one who guards his mouth [thinking before he speaks] protects
        his life;The one who opens his lips wide [and chatters without thinking]
        comes to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The soul (appetite) of the lazy person craves and gets nothing [for
        lethargy overcomes ambition],But the soul (appetite) of the diligent [who
        works willingly] is rich and abundantly supplied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A righteous man hates lies,But a wicked man is loathsome, and he
        acts shamefully.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Righteousness (being in right standing with God) guards the one whose
        way is blameless,But wickedness undermines and overthrows the sinner.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'There is one who pretends to be rich, yet has nothing at all;  Another
        pretends to be poor, yet has great wealth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The ransom for a man\u2019s life is his wealth,But the poor man does
        not even have to listen to a rebuke or threats [from the envious].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The light of the righteous [within him\u2014grows brighter and] rejoices,But
        the lamp of the wicked [is a temporary light and] goes out.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Through pride and presumption come nothing but strife,But [skillful
        and godly] wisdom is with those who welcome [well-advised] counsel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Wealth obtained by fraud dwindles,But he who gathers gradually by
        [honest] labor will increase [his riches].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Hope deferred makes the heart sick,But when desire is fulfilled,
        it is a tree of life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Whoever despises the word and counsel [of God] brings destruction
        upon himself,But he who [reverently] fears and respects the commandment [of
        God] will be rewarded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The teaching of the wise is a fountain and source of life,So that
        one may avoid the snares of death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Good understanding wins favor [from others],But the way of the unfaithful
        is hard [like barren, dry soil].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Every prudent and self-disciplined man acts with knowledge,But a
        [closed-minded] fool [who refuses to learn] displays his foolishness [for
        all to see].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'A wicked messenger falls into hardship,But a faithful ambassador
        brings healing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Poverty and shame will come to him who refuses instruction and discipline,But
        he who accepts and learns from reproof or censure is honored.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Desire realized is sweet to the soul;But it is detestable to fools
        to turn away from evil [which they have planned].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He who walks [as a companion] with wise men will be wise,But the
        companions of [conceited, dull-witted] fools [are fools themselves and] will
        experience harm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Adversity pursues sinners,But the [consistently] upright will be
        rewarded with prosperity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "A good man leaves an inheritance to his children\u2019s children,And
        the wealth of the sinner is stored up for [the hands of] the righteous.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Abundant food is in the fallow (uncultivated) ground of the poor,But
        [without protection] it is swept away by injustice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He who withholds the rod [of discipline] hates his son,But he who
        loves him disciplines and trains him diligently and appropriately [with wisdom
        and love].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: The [consistently] righteous has enough to satisfy his appetite,But
        the stomach of the wicked is in need [of bread].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked'
      title: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: '  The wise woman builds her house [on a foundation of godly precepts,
        and her household thrives],But the foolish one [who lacks spiritual insight]
        tears it down with her own hands [by ignoring godly principles].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He who walks in uprightness [reverently] fears the Lord [and obeys
        and worships Him with profound respect],But he who is devious in his ways
        despises Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the mouth of the [arrogant] fool [who rejects God] is a rod for
        his back,But the lips of the wise [when they speak with godly wisdom] will
        protect them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Where there are no oxen, the manger is clean,But much revenue [because
        of good crops] comes by the strength of the ox.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A faithful and trustworthy witness will not lie,But a false witness
        speaks lies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'A scoffer seeks wisdom and finds none [for his ears are closed to
        wisdom],But knowledge is easy for one who understands [because he is willing
        to learn].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Leave the presence of a [shortsighted] fool,For you will not find
        knowledge or hear godly wisdom from his lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The wisdom of the sensible is to understand his way,But the foolishness
        of [shortsighted] fools is deceit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Fools mock sin [but sin mocks the fools],But among the upright there
        is good will and the favor and blessing of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The heart knows its own bitterness,And no stranger shares its joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The house of the wicked will be overthrown,But the tent of the upright
        will thrive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'There is a way which seems right to a man and appears straight before
        him,But its end is the way of death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Even in laughter the heart may be in pain,And the end of joy may
        be grief.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The backslider in heart will have his fill with his own [rotten]
        ways,But a good man will be satisfied with his ways [the godly thought and
        action which his heart pursues and in which he delights].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The naive or inexperienced person [is easily misled and] believes
        every word he hears,But the prudent man [is discreet and astute and] considers
        well where he is going.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'A wise man suspects danger and cautiously avoids evil,But the fool
        is arrogant and careless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'A quick-tempered man acts foolishly and without self-control,And
        a man of wicked schemes is hated.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The naive [are unsophisticated and easy to exploit and] inherit foolishness,But
        the sensible [are thoughtful and far-sighted and] are crowned with knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The evil will bow down before the good,And the wicked [will bow down]
        at the gates of the righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The poor man is hated even by his neighbor,But those who love the
        rich are many.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He who despises his neighbor sins [against God and his fellow man],But
        happy [blessed and favored by God] is he who is gracious and merciful to
        the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Do they not go astray who devise evil and wander from the way of
        righteousness?But kindness and truth will be to those who devise good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In all labor there is profit,But mere talk leads only to poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The crown of the wise is their wealth [of wisdom],But the foolishness
        of [closed-minded] fools is [nothing but] folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'A truthful witness saves lives,But he who speaks lies is treacherous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'In the [reverent] fear of the Lord there is strong confidence,And
        His children will [always] have a place of refuge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The [reverent] fear of the Lord [that leads to obedience and worship]
        is a fountain of life,So that one may avoid the snares of death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "In a multitude of people is a king\u2019s glory,But in a lack of
        people is a [pretentious] prince\u2019s ruin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He who is slow to anger has great understanding [and profits from
        his self-control],But he who is quick-tempered exposes and exalts his foolishness
        [for all to see].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'A calm and peaceful and tranquil heart is life and health to the
        body,But passion and envy are like rottenness to the bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'He who oppresses the poor taunts and insults his Maker,But he who
        is kind and merciful and gracious to the needy honors Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The wicked is overthrown through his wrongdoing,But the righteous
        has hope and confidence and a refuge [with God] even in death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Wisdom rests [silently] in the heart of one who has understanding,But
        what is in the heart of [shortsighted] fools is made known.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Righteousness [moral and spiritual integrity and virtuous character]
        exalts a nation,But sin is a disgrace to any people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "The king\u2019s favor and good will are toward a servant who acts
        wisely and discreetly,But his anger and wrath are toward him who acts shamefully."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked'
      title: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: '  A soft and gentle and thoughtful answer turns away wrath,But harsh
        and painful and careless words stir up anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The tongue of the wise speaks knowledge that is pleasing and acceptable,But
        the [babbling] mouth of fools spouts folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The eyes of the Lord are in every place,Watching the evil and the
        good [in all their endeavors].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'A soothing tongue [speaking words that build up and encourage] is
        a tree of life,But a perversive tongue [speaking words that overwhelm and
        depress] crushes the spirit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "A [flippant, arrogant] fool rejects his father\u2019s instruction
        and correction,But he who [is willing to learn and] regards and keeps in
        mind a reprimand acquires good sense.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Great and priceless treasure is in the house of the [consistently]
        righteous one [who seeks godly instruction and grows in wisdom],But trouble
        is in the income of the wicked one [who rejects the laws of God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The lips of the wise spread knowledge [sifting it as chaff from the
        grain];But the hearts of [shortsighted] fools are not so.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The sacrifice of the wicked is hateful and exceedingly offensive
        to the Lord,But the prayer of the upright is His delight!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The way [of life] of the wicked is hateful and exceedingly offensive
        to the Lord,But He loves one who pursues righteousness [personal integrity,
        moral courage and honorable character].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'There is severe discipline for him who turns from the way [of righteousness];And
        he who hates correction will die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Sheol (the nether world, the place of the dead) and Abaddon (the
        abyss, the place of eternal punishment) lie open before the Lord\u2014How
        much more the hearts and inner motives of the children of men.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A scoffer [unlike a wise man] resents one who rebukes him and tries
        to teach him;Nor will he go to the wise [for counsel and instruction].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'A heart full of joy and goodness makes a cheerful face,But when a
        heart is full of sadness the spirit is crushed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The mind of the intelligent and discerning seeks knowledge and eagerly
        inquires after it,But the mouth of the [stubborn] fool feeds on foolishness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'All the days of the afflicted are bad,But a glad heart has a continual
        feast [regardless of the circumstances].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Better is a little with the [reverent, worshipful] fear of the LordThan
        great treasure and trouble with it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Better is a dinner of vegetables and herbs where love is presentThan
        a fattened ox served with hatred.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'A hot-tempered man stirs up strife,But he who is slow to anger and
        patient calms disputes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The way of the lazy is like a hedge of thorns [it pricks, lacerates,
        and entangles him],But the way [of life] of the upright is smooth and open
        like a highway.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'A wise son makes a father glad,But a foolish man despises his mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Foolishness is joy to him who is without heart and lacks [intelligent,
        common] sense,But a man of understanding walks uprightly [making his course
        straight].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Without consultation and wise advice, plans are frustrated,But with
        many counselors they are established and succeed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "A man has joy in giving an appropriate answer,And how good and delightful
        is a word spoken at the right moment\u2014how good it is!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The [chosen] path of life leads upward for the wise,That he may keep
        away from Sheol (the nether world, the place of the dead) below.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The Lord will tear down the house of the proud and arrogant (self-righteous),But
        He will establish and protect the boundaries [of the land] of the [godly]
        widow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Evil plans and thoughts of the wicked are exceedingly vile and offensive
        to the Lord,But pure words are pleasant words to Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He who profits unlawfully brings suffering to his own house,But he
        who hates bribes [and does not receive nor pay them] will live.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The heart of the righteous thinks carefully about how to answer [in
        a wise and appropriate and timely way],But the [babbling] mouth of the wicked
        pours out malevolent things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The Lord is far from the wicked [and distances Himself from them],But
        He hears the prayer of the [consistently] righteous [that is, those with
        spiritual integrity and moral courage].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The light of the eyes rejoices the hearts of others,And good news
        puts fat on the bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The ear that listens to and learns from the life-giving rebuke (reprimand,
        censure)Will remain among the wise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He who neglects and ignores instruction and discipline despises himself,But
        he who learns from rebuke acquires understanding [and grows in wisdom].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: The [reverent] fear of the Lord [that is, worshiping Him and regarding
        Him as truly awesome] is the instruction for wisdom [its starting point and
        its essence];And before honor comes humility.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked'
      title: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: '  The plans and reflections of the heart belong to man,But the [wise]
        answer of the tongue is from the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'All the ways of a man are clean and innocent in his own eyes [and
        he may see nothing wrong with his actions],But the Lord weighs and examines
        the motives and intents [of the heart and knows the truth].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Commit your works to the Lord [submit and trust them to Him],And
        your plans will succeed [if you respond to His will and guidance].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Lord has made everything for its own purpose,Even the wicked
        [according to their role] for the day of evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Everyone who is proud and arrogant in heart is disgusting and exceedingly
        offensive to the Lord;Be assured he will not go unpunished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'By mercy and lovingkindness and truth [not superficial ritual] wickedness
        is cleansed from the heart,And by the fear of the Lord one avoids evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When a man\u2019s ways please the Lord,He makes even his enemies
        to be at peace with him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Better is a little with righteousnessThan great income [gained] with
        injustice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "A man\u2019s mind plans his way [as he journeys through life],But
        the Lord directs his steps and establishes them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'A divine decision [given by God] is on the lips of the king [as His
        representative];His mouth should not be unfaithful or unjust in judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "A just balance and [honest] scales are the Lord\u2019s;All the weights
        of the bag are His concern [established by His eternal principles].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'It is repulsive [to God and man] for kings to behave wickedly,For
        a throne is established on righteousness (right standing with God).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Righteous lips are the delight of kings,And he who speaks right is
        loved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The wrath of a king is like a messenger of death,But a wise man will
        appease it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "In the light of the king\u2019s face is life,And his favor is like
        a cloud bringing the spring rain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'How much better it is to get wisdom than gold!And to get understanding
        is to be chosen above silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The highway of the upright turns away and departs from evil;He who
        guards his way protects his life (soul).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Pride goes before destruction,And a haughty spirit before a fall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'It is better to be humble in spirit with the lowlyThan to divide
        the spoil with the proud (haughty, arrogant).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He who pays attention to the word [of God] will find good,And blessed
        (happy, prosperous, to be admired) is he who trusts [confidently] in the
        Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The wise in heart will be called understanding,And sweet speech increases
        persuasiveness and learning [in both speaker and listener].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Understanding (spiritual insight) is a [refreshing and boundless]
        wellspring of life to those who have it,But to give instruction and correction
        to fools is foolishness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The heart of the wise instructs his mouth [in wisdom]And adds persuasiveness
        to his lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Pleasant words are like a honeycomb,Sweet and delightful to the soul
        and healing to the body.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'There is a way which seems right to a man and appears straight before
        him,But its end is the way of death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The appetite of a worker works for him,For his hunger urges him on.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'A worthless man devises and digs up evil,And the words on his lips
        are like a scorching fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'A perverse man spreads strife,And one who gossips separates intimate
        friends.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'A violent and exceedingly covetous man entices his neighbor [to sin],And
        leads him in a way that is not good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'He who [slyly] winks his eyes does so to plot perverse things;And
        he who compresses his lips [as if in a secret signal] brings evil to pass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The silver-haired head is a crown of splendor and glory;It is found
        in the way of righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He who is slow to anger is better and more honorable than the mighty
        [soldier],And he who rules and controls his own spirit, than he who captures
        a city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: The lot is cast into the lap,  But its every decision is from the
        Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked'
      title: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: '  Better is a dry morsel [of food served] with quietness and peaceThan
        a house full of feasting [served] with strife and contention.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A wise servant will rule over the [unworthy] son who acts shamefully
        and brings disgrace [to the family]And [the worthy servant] will share in
        the inheritance among the brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The refining pot is for silver and the furnace for gold,But the Lord
        tests hearts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'An evildoer listens closely to wicked lips;And a liar pays attention
        to a destructive and malicious tongue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Whoever mocks the poor taunts his Maker,And he who rejoices at [another\u2019s]
        disaster will not go unpunished.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Grandchildren are the crown of aged men,And the glory of children
        is their fathers [who live godly lives].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Excellent speech does not benefit a fool [who is spiritually blind],Much
        less do lying lips benefit a prince.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'A bribe is like a bright, precious stone in the eyes of its owner;Wherever
        he turns, he prospers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He who covers and forgives an offense seeks love,But he who repeats
        or gossips about a matter separates intimate friends.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'A reprimand goes deeper into one who has understanding and a teachable
        spiritThan a hundred lashes into a fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'A rebellious man seeks only evil;Therefore a cruel messenger will
        be sent against him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let a man meet a [ferocious] bear robbed of her cubsRather than the
        [angry, narcissistic] fool in his folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Whoever returns evil for good,Evil will not depart from his house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The beginning of strife is like letting out water [as from a small
        break in a dam; first it trickles and then it gushes];Therefore abandon the
        quarrel before it breaks out and tempers explode.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He who justifies the wicked, and he who condemns the righteousAre
        both repulsive to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Why is there money in the hand of a fool to buy wisdom,When he has
        no common sense or even a heart for it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'A friend loves at all times,And a brother is born for adversity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'A man lacking common sense gives a pledgeAnd becomes guarantor [for
        the debt of another] in the presence of his neighbor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He who loves transgression loves strife and is quarrelsome;He who
        [proudly] raises his gate seeks destruction [because of his arrogant pride].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He who has a crooked mind finds no good,And he who is perverted in
        his language falls into evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He who becomes the parent of a fool [who is spiritually blind] does
        so to his sorrow,And the father of a fool [who is spiritually blind] has
        no joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'A happy heart is good medicine and a joyful mind causes healing,But
        a broken spirit dries up the bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'A wicked man receives a bribe from the [hidden] pocketTo pervert
        the ways of justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '[Skillful and godly] wisdom is in the presence of a person of understanding
        [and he recognizes it],But the eyes of a [thickheaded] fool are on the ends
        of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'A foolish son is a grief and anguish to his fatherAnd bitterness
        to her who gave birth to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'It is also not good to fine the righteous,Nor to strike the noble
        for their uprightness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He who has knowledge restrains and is careful with his words,And
        a man of understanding and wisdom has a cool spirit (self-control, an even
        temper).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Even a [callous, arrogant] fool, when he keeps silent, is considered
        wise;When he closes his lips he is regarded as sensible (prudent, discreet)
        and a man of understanding.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked'
      title: Contrast the Upright and the Wicked
      number: 1
      content: '  He who [willfully] separates himself [from God and man] seeks his
        own desire,He quarrels against all sound wisdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A [closed-minded] fool does not delight in understanding,But only
        in revealing his personal opinions [unwittingly displaying his self-indulgence
        and his stupidity].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When the wicked man comes [to the depth of evil], contempt [of all
        that is pure and good] also comes,And with inner baseness (dishonor) comes
        outer shame (scorn).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The words of a man\u2019s mouth are like deep waters [copious and
        difficult to fathom];The fountain of [mature, godly] wisdom is like a bubbling
        stream [sparkling, fresh, pure, and life-giving].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'To show respect to the wicked person is not good,Nor to push aside
        and deprive the righteous of justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "A fool\u2019s lips bring contention and strife,And his mouth invites
        a beating.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "A fool\u2019s mouth is his ruin,And his lips are the snare of his
        soul.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The words of a whisperer (gossip) are like dainty morsels [to be
        greedily eaten];They go down into the innermost chambers of the body [to
        be remembered and mused upon].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He who is careless in his workIs a brother to him who destroys.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The name of the Lord is a strong tower;The righteous runs to it and
        is safe and set on high [far above evil].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The rich man\u2019s wealth is his strong city,And like a high wall
        [of protection] in his own imagination and conceit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Before disaster the heart of a man is haughty and filled with self-importance,But
        humility comes before honor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "He who answers before he hears [the facts]\u2014It is folly and shame
        to him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The spirit of a man sustains him in sickness,But as for a broken
        spirit, who can bear it?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The mind of the prudent [always] acquires knowledge,And the ear of
        the wise [always] seeks knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "A man\u2019s gift [given in love or courtesy] makes room for himAnd
        brings him before great men.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The first one to plead his case seems right,  Until another comes
        and cross-examines him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  To cast lots puts an end to quarrelsAnd decides between powerful
        contenders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'A brother offended is harder to win over than a fortified city,And
        contentions [separating families] are like the bars of a castle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "A man\u2019s stomach will be satisfied with the fruit of his mouth;He
        will be satisfied with the consequence of his words.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Death and life are in the power of the tongue,And those who love
        it and indulge it will eat its fruit and bear the consequences of their words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He who finds a [true and faithful] wife finds a good thingAnd obtains
        favor and approval from the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The poor man pleads,But the rich man answers roughly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: The man of too many friends [chosen indiscriminately] will be broken
        in pieces and come to ruin,But there is a [true, loving] friend who [is reliable
        and] sticks closer than a brother.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: On Life and Conduct'
      title: On Life and Conduct
      number: 1
      content: '  Better is a poor man who walks in his integrityThan a [rich] man
        who is twisted in his speech and is a [shortsighted] fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Also it is not good for a person to be without knowledge,And he who
        hurries with his feet [acting impulsively and proceeding without caution
        or analyzing the consequences] sins (misses the mark).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The foolishness of man undermines his way [ruining whatever he undertakes];Then
        his heart is resentful and rages against the Lord [for, being a fool, he
        blames the Lord instead of himself].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Wealth makes many friends,But a poor man is separated from his friend.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A false witness will not go unpunished,And he who breathes out lies
        will not escape.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Many will seek the favor of a generous and noble man,And everyone
        is a friend to him who gives gifts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the brothers of a poor man hate him;How much more do his friends
        abandon him!He pursues them with words, but they are gone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He who gains wisdom and good sense loves (preserves) his own soul;He
        who keeps understanding will find good and prosper.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'A false witness will not go unpunished,And he who breathes lies will
        perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Luxury is not fitting for a fool;Much less for a slave to rule over
        princes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Good sense and discretion make a man slow to anger,And it is his
        honor and glory to overlook a transgression or an offense [without seeking
        revenge and harboring resentment].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The king\u2019s wrath terrifies like the roaring of a lion,But his
        favor is as [refreshing and nourishing as] dew on the grass.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'A foolish (ungodly) son is destruction to his father,And the contentions
        of a [quarrelsome] wife are like a constant dripping [of water].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'House and wealth are the inheritance from fathers,But a wise, understanding,
        and sensible wife is [a gift and blessing] from the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Laziness casts one into a deep sleep [unmindful of lost opportunity],And
        the idle person will suffer hunger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He who keeps and obeys the commandment [of the Lord] keeps (guards)
        his own life,But he who is careless of his ways and conduct will die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He who is gracious and lends a hand to the poor lends to the Lord,And
        the Lord will repay him for his good deed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Discipline and teach your son while there is hope,And do not [indulge
        your anger or resentment by imposing inappropriate punishment nor] desire
        his destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  A man of great anger will bear the penalty [for his quick temper
        and lack of self-control];For if you rescue him [and do not let him learn
        from the consequences of his action], you will only have to rescue him over
        and over again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Listen to counsel, receive instruction, and accept correction,That
        you may be wise in the time to come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Many plans are in a man\u2019s mind,But it is the Lord\u2019s purpose
        for him that will stand (be carried out).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'That which is desirable in a man is his loyalty and unfailing love,But
        it is better to be a poor man than a [wealthy] liar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The fear of the Lord  leads to life,So that one may sleep satisfied,
        untouched by evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The lazy man buries his hand in the [food] dish,But will not even
        bring it to his mouth again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Strike a scoffer [for refusing to learn], and the naive may [be warned
        and] become prudent;Reprimand one who has understanding and a teachable spirit,
        and he will gain knowledge and insight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He who assaults his father and chases away his motherIs a son who
        brings shame and disgrace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Cease listening, my son, to instruction and discipline  And you will
        stray from the words of knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'A wicked and worthless witness mocks justice,And the mouth of the
        wicked spreads iniquity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Judgments are prepared for scoffers,And beatings for the backs of
        [thickheaded] fools.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: On Life and Conduct'
      title: On Life and Conduct
      number: 1
      content: '  Wine is a mocker, strong drink a riotous brawler;And whoever is
        intoxicated by it is not wise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The terror of a king is like the roaring of a lion;Whoever provokes
        him to anger forfeits his own life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It is an honor for a man to keep away from strife [by handling situations
        with thoughtful foresight],But any fool will [start a] quarrel [without regard
        for the consequences].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The lazy man does not plow when the winter [planting] season arrives;So
        he begs at the [next] harvest and has nothing [to reap].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A plan (motive, wise counsel) in the heart of a man is like water
        in a deep well,But a man of understanding draws it out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Many a man proclaims his own loyalty and goodness,But who can find
        a faithful and trustworthy man?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The righteous man who walks in integrity and lives life in accord
        with his [godly] beliefs\u2014How blessed [happy and spiritually secure]
        are his children after him [who have his example to follow].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'A [discerning] king who sits on the throne of judgmentSifts all evil
        [like chaff] with his eyes [and cannot be easily fooled].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Who can say, \u201CI have cleansed my heart,I am pure from my sin?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Differing weights [one for buying and another for selling] and differing
        measures,Both of them are detestable and offensive to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Even a boy is known and distinguished by his acts,Whether his conduct
        is pure and right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The hearing ear and the seeing eye,The [omnipotent] Lord has made
        both of them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Do not love [excessive] sleep, or you will become poor;Open your
        eyes [so that you can do your work] and you will be satisfied with bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CIt is [almost] worthless, it is [almost] worthless,\u201D says
        the buyer [as he negotiates the price];But when he goes his way, then he
        boasts [about his bargain].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'There is gold, and an abundance of pearls,But the lips of knowledge
        are a vessel of preciousness [the most precious of all].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "[The judge tells the creditor], \u201CTake the clothes of one who
        is surety for a stranger;And hold him in pledge [when he guarantees a loan]
        for foreigners.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Food gained by deceit is sweet to a man,But afterward his mouth will
        be filled with gravel [just as sin may be sweet at first, but later its consequences
        bring despair].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Plans are established by counsel;So make war [only] with wise guidance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He who goes about as a gossip reveals secrets;Therefore do not associate
        with a gossip [who talks freely or flatters].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Whoever curses his father or his mother,His lamp [of life] will be
        extinguished in time of darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'An inheritance hastily gained [by greedy, unjust means] at the beginningWill
        not be blessed in the end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Do not say, \u201CI will repay evil\u201D;Wait [expectantly] for
        the Lord, and He will rescue and save you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Differing weights are detestable and offensive to the Lord,And fraudulent
        scales are not good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Man\u2019s steps are ordered and ordained by the Lord.How then can
        a man [fully] understand his way?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "It is a trap for a man to [speak a vow of consecration and] say rashly,
        \u201CIt is holy!\u201DAnd [not until] afterward consider [whether he can
        fulfill it].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'A wise king sifts out the wicked [from among the good]And drives
        the [threshing] wheel over them [to separate the chaff from the grain].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The spirit (conscience) of man is the lamp of the Lord,Searching
        and examining all the innermost parts of his being.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Loyalty and mercy, truth and faithfulness, protect the king,And he
        upholds his throne by lovingkindness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The glory of young men is their [physical] strength,And the honor
        of aged men is their gray head [representing wisdom and experience].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Blows that wound cleanse away evil,And strokes reach to the innermost
        parts.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: On Life and Conduct'
      title: On Life and Conduct
      number: 1
      content: "  The king\u2019s heart is like channels of water in the hand of
        the Lord;He turns it whichever way He wishes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Every man\u2019s way is right in his own eyes,But the Lord weighs
        and examines the hearts [of people and their motives].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'To do righteousness and justiceIs more acceptable to the Lord than
        sacrifice [for wrongs repeatedly committed].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Haughty and arrogant eyes and a proud heart,The lamp of the wicked
        [their self-centered pride], is sin [in the eyes of God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The plans of the diligent lead surely to abundance and advantage,But
        everyone who acts in haste comes surely to poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Acquiring treasures by a lying tongueIs a fleeting vapor, the seeking
        and pursuit of death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The violence of the wicked will [return to them and] drag them away
        [like fish caught in a net],Because they refuse to act with justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The way of the guilty is [exceedingly] crooked,But as for the pure,
        his conduct is upright.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'It is better to live in a corner of the housetop [on the flat roof,
        exposed to the weather]Than in a house shared with a quarrelsome (contentious)
        woman.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The soul of the wicked desires evil [like an addictive substance];His
        neighbor finds no compassion in his eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When the scoffer is punished, the naive [observes the lesson and]
        becomes wise;But when the wise and teachable person is instructed, he receives
        knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The righteous one keeps an eye on the house of the wicked\u2014How
        the wicked are cast down to ruin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Whoever shuts his ears at the cry of the poorWill cry out himself
        and not be answered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'A gift in secret subdues anger,And a bribe [hidden] in the pocket,
        strong wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When justice is done, it is a joy to the righteous (the upright,
        the one in right standing with God),But to the evildoers it is disaster.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'A man who wanders from the way of understanding (godly wisdom)Will
        remain in the assembly of the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'He who loves [only selfish] pleasure will become a poor man;He who
        loves and is devoted to wine and [olive] oil will not become rich.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The wicked become a ransom for the righteous,And the treacherous
        in the place of the upright [for they fall into their own traps].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'It is better to dwell in a desert landThan with a contentious and
        troublesome woman.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'There is precious treasure and oil in the house of the wise [who
        prepare for the future],But a short-sighted and foolish man swallows it up
        and wastes it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He who earnestly seeks righteousness and loyaltyFinds life, righteousness,
        and honor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'A wise man scales the city [walls] of the mightyAnd brings down the
        stronghold in which they trust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He who guards his mouth and his tongueGuards himself from troubles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CProud,\u201D \u201CHaughty,\u201D \u201CScoffer,\u201D are
        his namesWho acts with overbearing and insolent pride.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The desire of the lazy kills him,For his hands refuse to labor;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He craves all the day long [and does no work],But the righteous [willingly]
        gives and does not withhold [what he has].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The sacrifice of the wicked is detestable and offensive [to the Lord].How
        much more [unacceptable and insulting can it be] when he brings it with evil
        intention?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'A false witness will perish,But a man who listens to the truth will
        speak forever and go unchallenged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'A wicked man puts on a bold face,But as for the upright, he considers,
        directs, and establishes his way [with the confidence of integrity].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'There is no [human] wisdom or understandingOr counsel [that can prevail]
        against the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The horse is prepared for the day of battle,But deliverance and victory
        belong to the Lord.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: On Life and Conduct'
      title: On Life and Conduct
      number: 1
      content: '  A good name [earned by honorable behavior, godly wisdom, moral
        courage, and personal integrity] is more desirable than great riches;And
        favor is better than silver and gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The rich and poor have a common bond;The Lord is the Maker of them
        all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'A prudent and far-sighted person sees the evil [of sin] and hides
        himself [from it],But the naive continue on and are punished [by suffering
        the consequences of sin].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The reward of humility [that is, having a realistic view of one\u2019s
        importance] and the [reverent, worshipful] fear of the LordIs riches, honor,
        and life.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thorns and snares are in the way of the obstinate [for their lack
        of honor and their wrong-doing traps them];He who guards himself [with godly
        wisdom] will be far from them and avoid the consequences they suffer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Train up a child in the way he should go [teaching him to seek God\u2019s
        wisdom and will for his abilities and talents],Even when he is old he will
        not depart from it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The rich rules over the poor,And the borrower is servant to the lender.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He who sows injustice will reap [a harvest of] trouble,And the rod
        of his wrath [with which he oppresses others] will fail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He who is generous will be blessed,For he gives some of his food
        to the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Drive out the scoffer, and contention will go away;Even strife and
        dishonor will cease.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He who loves purity of heartAnd whose speech is gracious will have
        the king as his friend.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The eyes of the Lord keep guard over knowledge and the one who has
        it,But He overthrows the words of the treacherous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The lazy one [manufactures excuses and] says, \u201CThere is a lion
        outside!I will be killed in the streets [if I go out to work]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The mouth of an immoral woman is a deep pit [deep and inescapable];He
        who is cursed by the Lord [because of his adulterous sin] will fall into
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Foolishness is bound up in the heart of a child;The rod of discipline
        [correction administered with godly wisdom and lovingkindness] will remove
        it far from him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He who oppresses or exploits the poor to get more for himselfOr who
        gives to the rich [to gain influence and favor], will only come to poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Listen carefully and hear the words of the wise,And apply your mind
        to my knowledge;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For it will be pleasant if you keep them in mind [incorporating them
        as guiding principles];Let them be ready on your lips [to guide and strengthen
        yourself and others].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So that your trust and reliance and confidence may be in the Lord,I
        have taught these things to you today, even to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Have I not written to you excellent thingsIn counsels and knowledge,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'To let you know the certainty of the words of truth,That you may
        give a correct answer to him who sent you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Do not rob the poor because he is poor [and defenseless],Nor crush
        the afflicted [by legal proceedings] at the gate [where the city court is
        held],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the Lord will plead their caseAnd take the life of those who
        rob them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Do not even associate with a man given to angry outbursts;Or go [along]
        with a hot-tempered man,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Or you will learn his [undisciplined] waysAnd get yourself trapped
        [in a situation from which it is hard to escape].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Do not be among those who give pledges [involving themselves in others\u2019
        finances],Or among those who become guarantors for others\u2019 debts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If you have nothing with which to pay [another\u2019s debt when he
        defaults],Why should his creditor take your bed from under you?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Do not move the ancient landmark [at the boundary of the property]Which
        your fathers have set.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Do you see a man skillful and experienced in his work?He will stand
        [in honor] before kings;He will not stand before obscure men.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: On Life and Conduct'
      title: On Life and Conduct
      number: 1
      content: '  When you sit down to dine with a ruler,Consider carefully what
        is [set] before you;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For you will put a knife to your throatIf you are a man of great
        appetite.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do not desire his delicacies,For it is deceptive food [offered to
        you with questionable motives].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Do not weary yourself [with the overwhelming desire] to gain wealth;Cease
        from your own understanding of it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When you set your eyes on wealth, it is [suddenly] gone.For wealth
        certainly makes itself wingsLike an eagle that flies to the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do not eat the bread of a selfish man,Or desire his delicacies;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For as he thinks in his heart, so is he [in behavior\u2014one who
        manipulates].He says to you, \u201CEat and drink,\u201DYet his heart is not
        with you [but it is begrudging the cost].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The morsel which you have eaten you will vomit up,And you will waste
        your compliments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not speak in the ears of a fool,For he will despise the [godly]
        wisdom of your words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Do not move the ancient landmark [at the boundary of the property]And
        do not go into the fields of the fatherless [to take what is theirs],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For their Redeemer is strong and mighty;He will plead their case
        against you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Apply your heart to disciplineAnd your ears to words of knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Do not withhold discipline from the child;If you swat him with a
        reed-like rod [applied with godly wisdom], he will not die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You shall swat him with the reed-like rodAnd rescue his life from
        Sheol (the nether world, the place of the dead).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'My son, if your heart is wise,My heart will also be glad;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Yes, my heart will rejoiceWhen your lips speak right things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do not let your heart envy sinners [who live godless lives and have
        no hope of salvation],But [continue to] live in the [reverent, worshipful]
        fear of the Lord day by day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Surely there is a future [and a reward],And your hope and expectation
        will not be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Listen, my son, and be wise,And direct your heart in the way [of
        the Lord].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do not associate with heavy drinkers of wine,  Or with gluttonous
        eaters of meat,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the heavy drinker and the glutton will come to poverty,And the
        drowsiness [of overindulgence] will clothe one with rags.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Listen to your father, who sired you,And do not despise your mother
        when she is old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Buy truth, and do not sell it;Get wisdom and instruction and understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The father of the righteous will greatly rejoice,And he who sires
        a wise child will have joy in him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Let your father and your mother be glad,And let her who gave birth
        to you rejoice [in your wise and godly choices].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'My son, give me your heartAnd let your eyes delight in my ways,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For a prostitute is a deep pit,And an immoral woman is a narrow well.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'She lurks and lies in wait like a robber [who waits for prey],And
        she increases the faithless among men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Who has woe? Who has sorrow?Who has strife? Who has complaining?Who
        has wounds without cause?Whose eyes are red and dim?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Those who linger long over wine,Those who go to taste mixed wine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Do not look at wine when it is red,When it sparkles in the glass,When
        it goes down smoothly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'At the last it bites like a serpentAnd stings like a viper.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Your [drunken] eyes will see strange thingsAnd your mind will utter
        perverse things [untrue things, twisted things].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And you will be [as unsteady] as one who lies down in the middle
        of the sea,And [as vulnerable to disaster] as one who lies down on the top
        of a ship\u2019s mast, saying,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThey struck me, but I was not hurt!They beat me, but I did
        not feel it!When will I wake up?I will seek more wine.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Precepts and Warnings'
      title: Precepts and Warnings
      number: 1
      content: '  Do not be envious of evil men,Nor desire to be with them;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For their minds plot violence,And their lips talk of trouble [for
        the innocent].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Through [skillful and godly] wisdom a house [a life, a home, a family]
        is built,And by understanding it is established [on a sound and good foundation],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And by knowledge its rooms are filledWith all precious and pleasant
        riches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A wise man is strong,And a man of knowledge strengthens his power;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For by wise guidance you can wage your war,And in an abundance of
        [wise] counselors there is victory and safety.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Wisdom is too exalted for a [hardened, arrogant] fool;He does not
        open his mouth in the gate [where the city\u2019s rulers sit in judgment].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He who plans to do evilWill be called a schemer or deviser of evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The devising of folly is sin,And the scoffer is repulsive to men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If you are slack (careless) in the day of distress,Your strength
        is limited.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Rescue those who are being taken away to death,And those who stagger
        to the slaughter, Oh hold them back [from their doom]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "If you [claim ignorance and] say, \u201CSee, we did not know this,\u201DDoes
        He not consider it who weighs and examines the hearts and their motives?And
        does He not know it who guards your life and keeps your soul?And will He
        not repay [you and] every man according to his works?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'My son, eat honey, because it is good,And the drippings of the honeycomb
        are sweet to your taste.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Know that [skillful and godly] wisdom is [so very good] for your
        life and soul;If you find wisdom, then there will be a future and a reward,And
        your hope and expectation will not be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Do not lie in wait, O wicked man, against the dwelling of the righteous;Do
        not destroy his resting place;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For a righteous man falls seven times, and rises again,But the wicked
        stumble in time of disaster and collapse.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Do not rejoice and gloat when your enemy falls,And do not let your
        heart be glad [in self-righteousness] when he stumbles,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Or the Lord will see your gloating and be displeased,And turn His
        anger away from your enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Do not get upset because of evildoers,Or be envious of the wicked,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For there will be no future for the evil man;The lamp of the wicked
        will be put out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'My son, fear the Lord and the king;And do not associate with those
        who are given to change [of allegiance, and are revolutionary],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For their tragedy will rise suddenly,And who knows the punishment
        that both [the Lord and the king] will bring on the rebellious?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These also are sayings of the wise:To show partiality in judgment
        is not good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He who says to the wicked, \u201CYou are righteous,\u201DPeoples
        will curse him, nations will denounce him;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But to those [honorable judges] who rebuke the wicked, it will go
        well with them and they will find delight,And a good blessing will come upon
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He kisses the lips [and wins the hearts of people]Who gives a right
        and straightforward answer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Prepare your work outsideAnd get it ready for yourself in the field; 
        Afterward build your house and establish a home.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Do not be a witness against your neighbor without cause,And do not
        deceive with your lips [speak neither lies nor half-truths].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Do not say, \u201CI will do to him as he has done to me;I will pay
        the man back for his deed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I went by the field of the lazy man,And by the vineyard of the man
        lacking understanding and common sense;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And, behold, it was all overgrown with thorns,And nettles were covering
        its surface,And its stone wall was broken down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'When I saw, I considered it well;I looked and received instruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CYet a little sleep, a little slumber,A little folding of the
        hands to rest [and daydream],\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Then your poverty will come as a robber,And your want like an armed
        man.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Similitudes, Instructions'
      title: Similitudes, Instructions
      number: 1
      content: '  These are also the proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah
        king of Judah copied:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It is the glory of God to conceal a matter,But the glory of kings
        is to search out a matter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As the heavens for height and the earth for depth,So the hearts and
        minds of kings are unsearchable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Take away the dross from the silver,And there comes out [the pure
        metal for] a vessel for the silversmith [to shape].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Take away the wicked from before the king,And his throne will be
        established in righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do not be boastfully ambitious and claim honor in the presence of
        the king,And do not stand in the place of great men;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For it is better that it be said to you, \u201CCome up here,\u201DThan
        for you to be placed lower in the presence of the prince,Whom your eyes have
        seen.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Do not rush out to argue your case [before magistrates or judges];Otherwise
        what will you do in the end [when your case is lost and]When your neighbor
        (opponent) humiliates you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Argue your case with your neighbor himself [before you go to court];And
        do not reveal another\u2019s secret,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Or he who hears it will shame youAnd the rumor about you [and your
        action in court] will have no end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Like apples of gold in settings of silverIs a word spoken at the
        right time.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Like an earring of gold and an ornament of fine goldIs a wise reprover
        to an ear that listens and learns.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Like the cold of snow [brought from the mountains] in the time of
        harvest,So is a faithful messenger to those who send him;For he refreshes
        the life of his masters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Like clouds and wind without rainIs a man who boasts falsely of gifts
        [he does not give].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'By patience and a calm spirit a ruler may be persuaded,And a soft
        and gentle tongue breaks the bone [of resistance].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Have you found [pleasure sweet like] honey? Eat only as much as you
        need,Otherwise, being filled excessively, you vomit it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Let your foot seldom be in your neighbor\u2019s house,Or he will
        become tired of you and hate you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Like a club and a sword and a piercing arrowIs a man who testifies
        falsely against his neighbor (acquaintance).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Like a broken tooth or an unsteady footIs confidence in an unfaithful
        man in time of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Like one who takes off a garment in cold weather, or like [a reactive,
        useless mixture of] vinegar on soda,Is he who [thoughtlessly] sings [joyful]
        songs to a heavy heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'If your enemy is hungry, give him bread to eat;And if he is thirsty,
        give him water to drink;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For in doing so, you will heap coals of fire upon his head,And the
        Lord will reward you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The north wind brings forth rain;And a backbiting tongue, an angry
        countenance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'It is better to live in a corner of the housetop [on the flat roof,
        exposed to the weather]Than in a house shared with a quarrelsome (contentious)
        woman.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Like cold water to a thirsty soul,So is good news from a distant
        land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Like a muddied fountain and a polluted springIs a righteous man who
        yields and compromises his integrity before the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "It is not good to eat much honey,Nor is it glorious to seek one\u2019s
        own glory.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Like a city that is broken down and without walls [leaving it unprotected]Is
        a man who has no self-control over his spirit [and sets himself up for trouble].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Similitudes, Instructions'
      title: Similitudes, Instructions
      number: 1
      content: '  Like snow in summer and like rain in harvest,So honor is not fitting
        for a [shortsighted] fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Like the sparrow in her wandering, like the swallow in her flying,So
        the curse without cause does not come and alight [on the undeserving].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'A whip for the horse, a bridle for the donkey,And a rod for the backs
        of fools [who refuse to learn].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Do not answer [nor pretend to agree with the frivolous comments of]
        a [closed-minded] fool according to his folly,Otherwise you, even you, will
        be like him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Answer [and correct the erroneous concepts of] a fool according to
        his folly,Otherwise he will be wise in his own eyes [if he thinks you agree
        with him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He who sends a message by the hand of a foolCuts off his own feet
        (sabotages himself) and drinks the violence [it brings on himself as a consequence].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Like the legs which are useless to the lame,So is a proverb in the
        mouth of a fool [who cannot learn from its wisdom].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Like one who [absurdly] binds a stone in a sling [making it impossible
        to throw],So is he who [absurdly] gives honor to a fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Like a thorn that goes [without being felt] into the hand of a drunken
        man,So is a proverb in the mouth of a fool [who remains unaffected by its
        wisdom].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Like a [careless] archer who [shoots arrows wildly and] wounds everyone,So
        is he who hires a fool or those who [by chance just] pass by.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Like a dog that returns to his vomitIs a fool who repeats his foolishness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Do you see a man [who is unteachable and] wise in his own eyes and
        full of self-conceit?There is more hope for a fool than for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "The lazy person [who is self-indulgent and relies on lame excuses]
        says, \u201CThere is a lion in the road!A lion is in the open square [and
        if I go outside to work I will be killed]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'As the door turns on its hinges,So does the lazy person on his bed
        [never getting out of it].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The lazy person buries his hand in the dish [losing opportunity after
        opportunity];It wearies him to bring it back to his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The lazy person is wiser in his own eyesThan seven [sensible] men
        who can give a discreet answer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Like one who grabs a dog by the ears [and is likely to be bitten]Is
        he who, passing by, stops to meddle with a dispute that is none of his business.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Like a madman who throwsFirebrands, arrows, and death,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So is the man who deceives his neighbor (acquaintance, friend)And
        then says, \u201CWas I not joking?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For lack of wood the fire goes out,And where there is no whisperer
        [who gossips], contention quiets down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Like charcoal to hot embers and wood to fire,So is a contentious
        man to kindle strife.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The words of a whisperer (gossip) are like dainty morsels [to be
        greedily eaten];They go down into the innermost chambers of the body [to
        be remembered and mused upon].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Like a [common] clay vessel covered with the silver dross [making
        it appear silver when it has no real value]Are burning lips [murmuring manipulative
        words] and a wicked heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He who hates, disguises it with his lips,But he stores up deceit
        in his heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When he speaks graciously and kindly [to conceal his malice], do
        not trust him,For seven abominations are in his heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  Though his hatred covers itself with guile and deceit,His malevolence
        will be revealed openly before the assembly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Whoever digs a pit [for another man\u2019s feet] will fall into it,And
        he who rolls a stone [up a hill to do mischief], it will come back on him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: A lying tongue hates those it wounds and crushes,And a flattering
        mouth works ruin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warnings and Instructions'
      title: Warnings and Instructions
      number: 1
      content: '  Do not boast about tomorrow,For you do not know what a day may
        bring.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Let another praise you, and not your own mouth;A stranger, and not
        your own lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Stone is heavy and the sand weighty,But a fool\u2019s [unreasonable]
        wrath is heavier and more burdensome than both of them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Wrath is cruel and anger is an overwhelming flood,But who is able
        to endure and stand before [the sin of] jealousy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Better is an open reprimand [of loving correction]Than love that
        is hidden.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Faithful are the wounds of a friend [who corrects out of love and
        concern],But the kisses of an enemy are deceitful [because they serve his
        hidden agenda].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He who is satisfied loathes honey,But to the hungry soul any bitter
        thing is sweet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Like a bird that wanders from her nest [with its comfort and safety],So
        is a man who wanders from his home.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Oil and perfume make the heart glad;So does the sweetness of a friend\u2019s
        counsel that comes from the heart.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Do not abandon your own friend and your father\u2019s friend,And
        do not go to your brother\u2019s house in the day of your disaster.Better
        is a neighbor who is near than a brother who is far away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'My son, be wise, and make my heart glad,That I may reply to him who
        reproaches (reprimands, criticizes) me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'A prudent man sees evil and hides himself and avoids it,But the naive
        [who are easily misled] continue on and are punished [by suffering the consequences
        of sin].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "[The judge tells the creditor,] \u201CTake the garment of one who
        is surety (guarantees a loan) for a stranger;And hold him in pledge when
        he is surety for an immoral woman [for it is unlikely the debt will be repaid].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He who blesses his neighbor with a loud voice early in the morning,It
        will be counted as a curse to him [for it will either be annoying or his
        purpose will be suspect].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'A constant dripping on a day of steady rainAnd a contentious (quarrelsome)
        woman are alike;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Whoever attempts to restrain her [criticism] might as well try to
        stop the wind,And grasps oil with his right hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As iron sharpens iron,So one man sharpens [and influences] another
        [through discussion].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He who tends the fig tree will eat its fruit,And he who faithfully
        protects and cares for his master will be honored.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'As in water face reflects face,So the heart of man reflects man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Sheol (the place of the dead) and Abaddon (the underworld) are never
        satisfied;Nor are the eyes of man ever satisfied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The refining pot is for silver and the furnace for gold [to separate
        the impurities of the metal],And each is tested by the praise given to him
        [and his response to it, whether humble or proud].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Even though you pound a [hardened, arrogant] fool [who rejects wisdom]
        in a mortar with a pestle like grain,Yet his foolishness will not leave him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Be diligent to know the condition of your flocks,And pay attention
        to your herds;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For riches are not forever,Nor does a crown endure to all generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When the grass is gone, the new growth is seen,And herbs of the mountain
        are gathered in,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The lambs will supply wool for your clothing,And the goats will bring
        the price of a field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And there will be enough goats\u2019 milk for your food,For the food
        of your household,And for the maintenance of your maids."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warnings and Instructions'
      title: Warnings and Instructions
      number: 1
      content: '  The wicked flee when no one pursues them,But the righteous are
        as bold as a lion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When a land does wrong, it has many princes,But when the ruler is
        a man of understanding and knowledge, its stability endures.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'A poor man who oppresses and exploits the lowlyIs like a sweeping
        rain which leaves no food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Those who set aside the law [of God and man] praise the wicked,But
        those who keep the law [of God and man] struggle with them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Evil men do not understand justice,But they who long for and seek
        the Lord understand it fully.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Better is the poor who walks in his integrityThan he who is crooked
        and two-faced though he is rich.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He who keeps the law [of God and man] is a wise and discerning son,But
        he who is a companion of gluttons humiliates his father [and himself].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He who increases his wealth by interest and usury (excessive interest)Gathers
        it for him who is gracious to the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He who turns his ear away from listening to the law [of God and man],Even
        his prayer is repulsive [to God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He who leads the upright astray on an evil pathWill himself fall
        into his own pit,But the blameless will inherit good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The rich man [who is conceited and relies on his wealth instead of
        God] is wise in his own eyes,But the poor man who has understanding [because
        he relies on God] is able to see through him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When the righteous triumph, there is great glory and celebration;But
        when the wicked rise [to prominence], men hide themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He who conceals his transgressions will not prosper,But whoever confesses
        and turns away from his sins will find compassion and mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Blessed and favored by God is the man who fears [sin and its consequence]
        at all times,But he who hardens his heart [and is determined to sin] will
        fall into disaster.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Like a roaring lion and a charging bearIs a wicked ruler over a poor
        people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'A leader who is a great oppressor lacks understanding and common
        sense [and his wickedness shortens his days],But he who hates unjust gain
        will [be blessed and] prolong his days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'A man who is burdened with the guilt of human blood (murder)Will
        be a fugitive until death; let no one support him or give him refuge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He who walks blamelessly and uprightly will be kept safe,But he who
        is crooked (perverse) will suddenly fall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He who cultivates his land will have plenty of bread,But he who follows
        worthless people and frivolous pursuits will have plenty of poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'A faithful (right-minded) man will abound with blessings,But he who
        hurries to be rich will not go unpunished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'To have regard for one person over another and to show favoritism
        is not good,Because for a piece of bread a man will transgress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He who has an evil and envious eye hurries to be richAnd does not
        know that poverty will come upon him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'He who [appropriately] reprimands a [wise] man will afterward find
        more favorThan he who flatters with the tongue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "He who robs his father or his motherAnd says, \u201CThis is no sin,\u201DIs
        [not only a thief but also] the companion of a man who destroys.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'An arrogant and greedy man stirs up strife,But he who trusts in the
        Lord will be blessed and prosper.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He who trusts confidently in his own heart is a [dull, thickheaded]
        fool,But he who walks in [skillful and godly] wisdom will be rescued.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He who gives to the poor will never want,But he who shuts his eyes
        [from their need] will have many curses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: When the wicked rise [to power], men hide themselves;But when the
        wicked perish, the [consistently] righteous increase and become great.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warnings and Instructions'
      title: Warnings and Instructions
      number: 1
      content: '  He who hardens his neck and refuses instruction after being often
        reproved (corrected, criticized),Will suddenly be broken beyond repair.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When the righteous are in authority and become great, the people
        rejoice;But when the wicked man rules, the people groan and sigh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'A man who loves [skillful and godly] wisdom makes his father joyful,But
        he who associates with prostitutes wastes his wealth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The king establishes (stabilizes) the land by justice,But a man who
        takes bribes overthrows it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A man who flatters his neighbor [with smooth words intending to do
        harm]Is spreading a net for his own feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'By his wicked plan an evil man is trapped,But the righteous man sings
        and rejoices [for his plan brings good things to him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The righteous man cares for the rights of the poor,But the wicked
        man has no interest in such knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Scoffers set a city afire [by stirring up trouble],But wise men turn
        away anger [and restore order with their good judgment].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'If a wise man has a controversy with a foolish and arrogant man,The
        foolish man [ignores logic and fairness and] only rages or laughs, and there
        is no peace (rest, agreement).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The bloodthirsty hate the blameless [because of his integrity],But
        the upright are concerned for his life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'A [shortsighted] fool always loses his temper and displays his anger,But
        a wise man [uses self-control and] holds it back.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'If a ruler pays attention to lies [and encourages corruption],All
        his officials will become wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The poor man and the oppressor have this in common:The Lord gives
        light to the eyes of both.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If a king faithfully and truthfully judges the poor,His throne shall
        be established forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The rod and reproof (godly instruction) give wisdom,But a child who
        gets his own way brings shame to his mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When the wicked are in authority, transgression increases,But the
        righteous will see the downfall of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Correct your son, and he will give you comfort;Yes, he will delight
        your soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Where there is no vision [no revelation of God and His word], the
        people are unrestrained;But happy and blessed is he who keeps the law [of
        God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'A servant will not be corrected by words alone;For though he understands,
        he will not respond [nor pay attention].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do you see a [conceited] man who speaks quickly [offering his opinions
        or answering without thinking]?There is more hope for a [thickheaded] fool
        than for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He who pampers his slave from childhoodWill find him to be a son
        in the end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'An angry man stirs up strife,And a hot-tempered and undisciplined
        man commits many transgressions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "A man\u2019s pride and sense of self-importance will bring him down,But
        he who has a humble spirit will obtain honor.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Whoever is partner with a thief hates his own life;He hears the curse
        [when swearing an oath to testify], but discloses nothing [and commits perjury
        by omission].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The fear of man brings a snare,But whoever trusts in and puts his
        confidence in the Lord will be exalted and safe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Many seek the ruler\u2019s favor,But justice for man comes from the
        Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: An unjust man is repulsive to the righteous,And he who is upright
        in the way [of the Lord] is repulsive to the wicked.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Words of Agur'
      title: The Words of Agur
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of Agur the son of Jakeh, the oracle:  The man says to
        Ithiel, to Ithiel and to Ucal:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Surely I am more brutish and stupid than any man,And I do not have
        the understanding of a man [for I do not know what I do not know].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I have not learned [skillful and godly] wisdom,Nor do I have knowledge
        of the Holy One [who is the source of wisdom].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Who has ascended into heaven and descended?Who has gathered the wind
        in His fists?Who has bound the waters in His garment?Who has established
        all the ends of the earth?What is His name, and what is His Son\u2019s name?Certainly
        you know!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Every word of God is tested and refined [like silver];He is a shield
        to those who trust and take refuge in Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do not add to His words,Or He will reprove you, and you will be found
        a liar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Two things I have asked of You;Do not deny them to me before I die:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Keep deception and lies far from me;Give me neither poverty nor riches;Feed
        me with the food that is my portion,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So that I will not be full and deny You and say, \u201CWho is the
        Lord?\u201DOr that I will not be poor and steal,And so profane the name of
        my God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Do not slander or malign a servant before his master [stay out of
        another\u2019s personal life],Or he will curse you [for your interference],
        and you will be found guilty.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'There is a generation (class of people) that curses its fatherAnd
        does not bless its mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'There is a generation (class of people) that is pure in its own eyes,Yet
        is not washed from its filthiness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "There is a generation (class of people)\u2014oh, how lofty are their
        eyes!And their eyelids are raised in arrogance.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'There is a generation (class of people) whose teeth are like swordsAnd
        whose jaw teeth are like knives,To devour the afflicted from the earthAnd
        the needy from among men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The leech has two daughters,\u201CGive, give!\u201DThere are three
        things that are never satisfied,Four that do not say, \u201CIt is enough\u201D:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  Sheol, and the barren womb,Earth that is never satisfied with water,And
        fire that never says, \u201CIt is enough.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The eye that mocks a fatherAnd scorns a mother,The ravens of the
        valley will pick it out,And the young vultures will devour it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There are three things which are too astounding and unexpectedly
        wonderful for me,Four which I do not understand:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The way of an eagle in the air,The way of a serpent on a rock,The
        way of a ship in the middle of the sea,And the way of a man with a maid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "This is the way of an adulterous woman:She eats and wipes her mouthAnd
        says, \u201CI have done no wrong.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Under three things the earth is disquieted and quakes,And under four
        it cannot bear up:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Under a servant when he reigns,  Under a [spiritually blind] fool
        when he is filled with food,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Under an unloved woman when she gets married,And under a maidservant
        when she supplants her mistress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'There are four things that are small on the earth,But they are exceedingly
        wise:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The ants are not a strong people,Yet they prepare their food in the
        summer;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The shephanim are not a mighty folk,Yet they make their houses in
        the rocks;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The locusts have no king,Yet all of them go out in groups;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You may grasp the lizard with your hands,Yet it is in kings\u2019
        palaces.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'There are three things which are stately in step,Even four which
        are stately in their stride:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The lion, which is mighty among beastsAnd does not turn back before
        any;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The strutting rooster, the male goat also,And the king when his army
        is with him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'If you have foolishly exalted yourself,Or if you have plotted evil,
        put your hand on your mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Surely the churning of milk produces butter,And wringing the nose
        produces blood;So the churning of anger produces strife.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Words of Lemuel'
      title: The Words of Lemuel
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of King Lemuel, the oracle, which his mother taught him:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'What, O my son?And what, O son of my womb?And what [shall I advise
        you], O son of my vows?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do not give your [generative] strength to women [neither foreign
        wives in marriages of alliances, nor concubines],Nor your ways to that which
        destroys kings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'It is not for kings, O Lemuel,It is not for kings to drink wine,Or
        for rulers to desire strong drink,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Otherwise they drink and forget the law and its decrees,And pervert
        the rights and justice of all the afflicted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Give strong drink [as medicine] to him who is ready to pass away,And
        wine to him whose life is bitter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Let him drink and forget his povertyAnd no longer remember his trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Open your mouth for the mute,For the rights of all who are unfortunate
        and defenseless;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Description of a Worthy Woman'
      title: Description of a Worthy Woman
      number: 9
      content: 'Open your mouth, judge righteously,And administer justice for the
        afflicted and needy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  An excellent woman [one who is spiritual, capable, intelligent,
        and virtuous], who is he who can find her?Her value is more precious than
        jewels and her worth is far above rubies or pearls.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The heart of her husband trusts in her [with secure confidence],And
        he will have no lack of gain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'She comforts, encourages, and does him only good and not evilAll
        the days of her life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'She looks for wool and flaxAnd works with willing hands in delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "She is like the merchant ships [abounding with treasure];She brings
        her [household\u2019s] food from far away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'She rises also while it is still nightAnd gives food to her householdAnd
        assigns tasks to her maids.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'She considers a field before she buys or accepts it [expanding her
        business prudently];With her profits she plants fruitful vines in her vineyard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'She equips herself with strength [spiritual, mental, and physical
        fitness for her God-given task]And makes her arms strong.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'She sees that her gain is good;Her lamp does not go out, but it burns
        continually through the night [she is prepared for whatever lies ahead].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'She stretches out her hands to the distaff,And her hands hold the
        spindle [as she spins wool into thread for clothing].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'She opens and extends her hand to the poor,And she reaches out her
        filled hands to the needy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'She does not fear the snow for her household,For all in her household
        are clothed in [expensive] scarlet [wool].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'She makes for herself coverlets, cushions, and rugs of tapestry.Her
        clothing is linen, pure and fine, and purple [wool].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Her husband is known in the [city\u2019s] gates,When he sits among
        the elders of the land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'She makes [fine] linen garments and sells them;And supplies sashes
        to the merchants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Strength and dignity are her clothing and her position is strong
        and secure;And she smiles at the future [knowing that she and her family
        are prepared].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'She opens her mouth in [skillful and godly] wisdom,And the teaching
        of kindness is on her tongue [giving counsel and instruction].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'She looks well to how things go in her household,And does not eat
        the bread of idleness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Her children rise up and call her blessed (happy, prosperous, to
        be admired);Her husband also, and he praises her, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CMany daughters have done nobly, and well [with the strength
        of character that is steadfast in goodness],  But you excel them all.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Charm and grace are deceptive, and [superficial] beauty is vain,But
        a woman who fears the Lord [reverently worshiping, obeying, serving, and
        trusting Him with awe-filled respect], she shall be praised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Give her of the product of her hands,And let her own works praise
        her in the gates [of the city].
      comments: []
